          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>London</placeName>
                                        <date>17th Adar <add>?</add> 5611</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Revd. and Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">I had the pleasure of receiving yours of the
                                                  <date>4th:<lb/> March</date> on <date>Purim</date>
                                        day you will see that however I may be situated I do<lb/>
                                        not allow a post to let your subject unnoticed; of course I
                                        can say but<lb/> little this day since I wrote to you on
                                                  <date><sic>friday</sic></date> last, neither have
                                        I<lb/> had any reply to my second letter which I addressed
                                                  <persName>Mr. A. Hart</persName><lb/> on the
                                                  <date>19:th Adar</date>, the moment I do, you
                                        shall be made acquainted<lb/> with the contents trusting
                                        &amp; hoping <hi rend="underline">good</hi>
                                        <add>טוב</add> I noticed in yours wherein you<lb/> say "as
                                                  <persName>Mr. A: Hart</persName> denies having
                                        commissioned anyone to speak to<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. Morais.</persName>" I trust &amp; hope you
                                        will see to this point seriously, that<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. M's</persName> name will not be brought to
                                        question in any way particularly mine in<lb/> the slightest
                                        way do I wish it, for whatever I communicated to you
                                        was<lb/> in the strictest confidence and so <persName><hi
                                                  rend="underline">did
                                                  <persName>Morais</persName></hi></persName> when
                                        he opened his mind<lb/> to me as a <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >friend</hi>, relying on my honor he related to me
                                        the whole<lb/> from a beginning; now to the best of my
                                        recollection, I <sic>dont</sic> think this lady<lb/>
                                        <add>?</add>
                                        <persName>Mr. <hi rend="underline">A: Hart</hi></persName>
                                        but "she should write about it to a <persName>Mr.
                                                  Hart.</persName>" neither<lb/> was her commission
                                                  <hi rend="underline">direct</hi> to <persName>Mr.
                                                  M</persName>, she spoke to him on her having
                                        heard<lb/> him and thought he would do, but she was looking
                                                  <hi rend="underline">for some one</hi> as<lb/>
                                        they were in want of a Hazan, therefore pray do not let me
                                        have<lb/> any more to do with that lady <persName>Mrs.
                                                  Claudia</persName>, nor do not allow our<lb/> name
                                        to be mingled any further. I wish to be clear with
                                                  <persName>Mr. M</persName>:<lb/> and do not wish
                                        him to think in the least that I caused through my<lb/>
                                        correspondence the slightest confession I <hi
                                                  rend="underline">rely</hi> on <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >you</hi> to this, for things are<lb/> taken in so
                                        many views when there are so many parties all <add>על סלע
                                                  המחלוקות</add><lb/> pray neither expose any
                                        further the conduct of that lady towards me, for one</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>thing may stir the other. I delivered myself of our letter to
                                                  <persName>Mr. Peynado</persName><lb/> he was very
                                        thankful to me. I return you my <add>?</add> thanks for<lb/>
                                        your valuable and truly precious present I will write to you
                                        on this<lb/> on another occasion as I am a little disturbed
                                        this day my mind<lb/> is not adequate to write as I should
                                                  <add>?</add> in any way you think me<lb/> capable
                                        of serving you pray do not hesitate in the least as I
                                        shall<lb/> ever consider it a pleasure. I shall not forget
                                        your commission.<lb/> Wishing you most heartily to be the
                                        successful <add>?</add> and that all<lb/> your friends will
                                        support and uphold your <hi rend="underline">just
                                        cause</hi>. I do not make<lb/> any observations on the other
                                        points you wrote concerning <persName>Bowenfeld</persName> &amp;c<lb/>
                                        <persName>Dr. Raphael</persName> style &amp;c which I have
                                        much to say (and will do it) for<lb/> the cause I have
                                        assigned. I <hi rend="underline">hinted</hi> it to
                                                  <persName>Morais</persName> to mind what he
                                        did<lb/> I could not press much upon him as he might suppose
                                        it was <add>?</add><lb/> sake he has obtained permission for
                                        3 months from the school he teaches<lb/> and I believe some
                                        friends made him assume to defray all expenses<lb/> no doubt
                                        against this reaches you he must have had his trial<lb/> I
                                        shall be glad to hear the result our friend <persName>Mr.
                                                  Isaacs</persName> lectures<lb/> tomorrow morning
                                        at the new synagogue I have not seen him since<lb/> his
                                        return from <placeName>Holland</placeName>
                                        <add>ושלום רב</add>, I remain with all esteem &amp;
                                        regard</p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>לנו יקרב וישע רב</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Revd. &amp; dear sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">yours very faithfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">
                                        <persName role="author">David Meldola</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>We must bear in mind that perhaps when<lb/> the lady sent for
                                                  <persName>Morais</persName> it might have been in
                                        confidence therefore<lb/> I should not like on my part to
                                        betray the confidence of a friend.<lb/>
                                        <persName>Rabbi Nissim</persName> always enquires in his
                                        letters about your affairs.</p>
                    </body>
